### Trigger a full replication run for `Categories` from Northwind V4.
### The source is public; no delta field on the remote, so every run is
### a full refresh. Typically finishes in a second or two.
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/run
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Categories","mode":"full"}

### Query the locally replicated table — no remote hit.
GET http://localhost:4005/odata/v4/sales-intel/Categories?$orderby=categoryName

### Re-trigger — UPSERT keeps the table idempotent (no duplicates).
POST http://localhost:4005/pipeline/run
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Categories","mode":"full"}

### Inspect run history for Categories
GET http://localhost:4005/pipeline/Pipelines?$filter=name eq 'Categories'&$expand=runs($orderby=startTime desc;$top=3)
